    HomologicalComplex.mapBifunctorAssociator

    The associator for actions of bifunctors on homological complexes #

    In this file, we shall adapt the results of the file CategoryTheory.GradedObject.Associator to the case of homological complexes. Given functors F‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ : C‚ÇÅ ‚•§ C‚ÇÇ ‚•§ C‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ, G : C‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ ‚•§ C‚ÇÉ ‚•§ C‚ÇÑ, F : C‚ÇÅ ‚•§ C‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ ‚•§ C‚ÇÑ, G‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ : C‚ÇÇ ‚•§ C‚ÇÉ ‚•§ C‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ equipped with an isomorphism associator : bifunctorComp‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ F‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ G ‚âÖ bifunctorComp‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ F G‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ (which informally means that we have natural isomorphisms G(F‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ(X‚ÇÅ, X‚ÇÇ), X‚ÇÉ) ‚âÖ F(X‚ÇÅ, G‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ(X‚ÇÇ, X‚ÇÉ))), we define an isomorphism mapBifunctorAssociator from mapBifunctor (mapBifunctor K‚ÇÅ K‚ÇÇ F‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ) K‚ÇÉ G c‚ÇÑ to mapBifunctor K‚ÇÅ (mapBifunctor K‚ÇÇ K‚ÇÉ G‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ) F c‚ÇÑ when we have three homological complexes K‚ÇÅ : HomologicalComplex C‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÅ, K‚ÇÇ : HomologicalComplex C‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÇ and K‚ÇÉ : HomologicalComplex C‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÉ, assumptions TotalComplexShape c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ, TotalComplexShape c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÑ, TotalComplexShape c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ, TotalComplexShape c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÑ, and ComplexShape.Associative c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÑ about the complex shapes, and technical assumptions [HasGoodTrifunctor‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇObj F‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ G K‚ÇÅ K‚ÇÇ K‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÑ] and [HasGoodTrifunctor‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉObj F G‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ K‚ÇÅ K‚ÇÇ K‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÑ] about the commutation of certain functors to certain coproducts.

    The main application of these results shall be the construction of the associator for the monoidal category structure on homological complexes.
